The Houston Rockets withstood a 45-point game from Carmelo Anthony to win 109-106 and hand the  New
York Knicks  their fourth straight home defeat.  James Harden  scored 36 points and former Knicks point guard
Jeremy Lin added 21 off the bench for the Rockets (6-4) at
Madison Square Garden in New York last night.  Anthonyâ€™s points tally was the highest in the National
Basketball Association so far this season. He also had 10
rebounds for the Knicks (3-5), while Andrea Bargnani added 24
points and J.R. Smith contributed 15.  Chandler Parsons scored 22 points for the Rockets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
